+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Used `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` as the source of truth and classified all five visible threads before editing code. The resulting triage is recorded in `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`.
+
+## Thread Outcomes
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable. Fixed the fallback preview payload in `src/policy/preview.py`.
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`. No separate code path changed.
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete. Did not apply the outdated legacy-preview suggestion in `src/policy/approval_router.py`.
+- `T-214-04`: actionable. Added writable regression coverage in `tests/test_preview.py`.
+- `T-214-05`: actionable. Updated the fallback example in `docs/approval_policy.md`.
+
+## Code Changes
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`: `build_policy_preview` now normalizes the incoming approval state before delegating to the preview payload builder.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`: fallback responses now include `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`, matching the normalized policy payload shape.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`: added fallback assertions for preserved human-review fields and a regression test for `manual_review` normalization on the preview-unavailable path.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`: corrected the documented fallback JSON example and note text.
+
+## Verification
+
+Ran:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Result: `OK` (`Ran 5 tests`).
+
+## Constraints Honored
+
+- Did not modify `.github/review_export/`, `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md`, `tests/test_approval_router.py`, `AGENTS.md`, `Dockerfile`, `.scenario_variant`, `release_context/`, or `incident_context/`.
+- Did not add `legacy_preview_hint`.
+- Did not use the network.
